-Flying Boats and Seaplanes since 1910 (The Pocket Encyclopedia of World Aircraft in Color) Hardcover – 1971

Ever since the first seaplane flew in 1910 water-borne aircraft have exercised an appeal and fascination all their own. This book has a representative selection of Flying Boats and Seaplanes.

-Bombers 1914-19 Patrol and Reconnaissance Aircraft Hardcover – 1977

Second Revised edition (1977)

About the book: Small in size, but filled with information on patrol and reconnaissance aircraft statistics. With tons of detailed color photos, this guide displays the key bomber planes used between 1914 and 1919. Allied and Axis planes like the D.H.9A from Britain, the Albatros from Germany and the Caproni Ca 4 from Italy

Publisher: Blandford Press Poole Dorset
